2 SENATE BILL 363
1 Article – Economic Development
2 5–2501.
3 In this subtitle, “Commission” means the Maryland–Ireland Trade Commission.
4 5–2502.
5 (a) There is a Maryland–Ireland Trade Commission in the Department.
6 (b) The purpose of the Commission is to study and promote trade between
7 Maryland and Ireland.
8 5–2503.
9 (a) The Commission consists of the following members:
10 (1) the Secretary, or the Secretary’s designee;
11 (2) the Secretary of State, or the Secretary of State’s designee;
12 (3) [two members] ONE MEMBER of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by
13 the President of the Senate, who [have] HAS knowledge of organizations that promote Irish
14 affairs, or current or past involvement in organizations that promote Irish affairs, or [have]
15 HAS an interest in the well–being of trade relations between Maryland and Ireland;
16 (4) [two members] ONE MEMBER of the House of Delegates, appointed by
17 the Speaker of the House, who [have] HAS knowledge of organizations that promote Irish
18 affairs, or current or past involvement in organizations that promote Irish affairs, or [have]
19 HAS an interest in the well–being of trade relations between Maryland and Ireland; and
20 (5) the following members, appointed by the Governor, with the advice and
21 consent of the Senate:
22 (i) one representative of a public institution of higher education;
23 (ii) one representative of the Maryland Chamber of Commerce or its
24 successor organization; [and]
25 (iii) two representatives of the Irish–American community, who may
26 not be of the same political party; AND
27 (IV) TWO MEMBERS OF THE PRIVATE SECTOR.

SENATE BILL 363 3
1 (b) The chair and vice chair of the Commission shall be elected from among the
2 members of the Commission.
3 (c) A member of the Commission:
4 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Commission; but
5 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
6 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
7 (d) The Governor may remove an appointed member for incompetence,
8 misconduct, or failure to perform the duties of the position.
9 5–2504.
10 (a) The Commission shall study and make recommendations regarding:
11 (1) advancing bilateral trade and investment between Maryland and
12 Ireland;
13 (2) initiating joint action on policy issues of mutual interest to Maryland
14 and Ireland;
15 (3) promoting business and academic exchanges between Maryland and
16 Ireland;
17 (4) encouraging mutual economic support between Maryland and Ireland;
18 (5) encouraging mutual investment in the infrastructure of Maryland and
19 Ireland; and
20 (6) other issues as determined by the Commission.
21 (b) On or before December 1, 2025, AND EACH DECEMBER 1 THEREAFTER, the
22 Commission shall report its findings and recommendations to the Governor and, in
23 accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the General Assembly.
24 Chapter 409 of the Acts of 2024
25 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
26 October 1, 2024. It shall remain effective for a period of [2] 4 years and, at the end of
27 September 30, [2026] 2028, this Act, with no further action required by the General
28 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
29 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
30 1, 2026.

